Seniors and Senior Families!

We will be making deliveries this coming Monday, June 1, from 5-8pm.

We will be bringing your Diplomas, Senior Yard Signs, and Photos from Graduation to you!

We would like to snap a quick picture of you with your sign and diploma for our social media.

Seniors to avoid delays in receiving your diploma, please settle any debts owed. Senior parents were sent email invoices for debts through our “Cube” account for easy payment.

Please email me at walkerb@felicityohioschools.org if you will not be home on Monday, June 1 from 5-8pm so that other arrangements can be made.

Have a great day!
Principal Walker

post_text: Please share this information with your neighbors that may be in need, perhaps this will help their student as we navigate these remote learning opportunities. Families with school children currently without internet or WiFi, this may be helpful to gaining access to both at home. Contact, Spectrum at 844-488-8395. Charter Spectrum will offer free Spectrum broadband and Wi-Fi access for 60 days to households with K-12 and/or college students who do not already have a Spectrum broadband subscription at any service level up to 100 Mbps. To enroll call 1-844-488-8395. Installation fees will be waived for new student households.

shared_text:
Felicity Franklin FFA
October 30, 2019 at 11:56 AM ·

Congratulations to the Drum line who advanced to the semi finals!!! They will perform tomorrow at 1:00 on Lucas Oil main stage and then at approx. 5:45 for the actual competition, also on the main stage.

A huge shout out to Mark & Kristin Baird for coordinating, chaperoning and driving them around this week and helping with everything from tryouts to practices.

A BIG thanks to Lee Myers for designing and fabricating the awesome cart for the bass drums for easy transport around the city and higher sound quality, as well as Garrett Taulbee, Charlie Troxell and Ethan Simmerman for their help!

We wouldn’t have gotten this act off the ground without the help of David Parks and Stacie Taylor this summer! Thanks for all the hours on a really crammed weekend to make this happen and all the opportunities to perform since then!

And thanks to Ben Backus, HS band director, for helping give them the background needed and tweak the musical quality of the performance.

#ittakesavillage
text:
Felicity Franklin FFA
October 30, 2019 at 11:56 AM ·

Congratulations to the Drum line who advanced to the semi finals!!! They will perform tomorrow at 1:00 on Lucas Oil main stage and then at approx. 5:45 for the actual competition, also on the main stage.

A huge shout out to Mark & Kristin Baird for coordinating, chaperoning and driving them around this week and helping with everything from tryouts to practices.

A BIG thanks to Lee Myers for designing and fabricating the awesome cart for the bass drums for easy transport around the city and higher sound quality, as well as Garrett Taulbee, Charlie Troxell and Ethan Simmerman for their help!

We wouldn’t have gotten this act off the ground without the help of David Parks and Stacie Taylor this summer! Thanks for all the hours on a really crammed weekend to make this happen and all the opportunities to perform since then!

And thanks to Ben Backus, HS band director, for helping give them the background needed and tweak the musical quality of the performance.

#ittakesavillage

post_text: FFHS is excited to announce that we have entered into a partnership with the YMCA! The YMCA of Greater Cincinnati has been awarded a special grant through the State of Ohio, Department of Education, 21st Century Community Learning Centers. The 21st CCLC Grant will help us provide numerous opportunities for after-school tutoring, new and improved after-school clubs/activities, ACT Prep, College & Career Visits, Career Exploration, summer opportunities and more, without spending local tax dollars! The first step for the YMCA is for the YMCA to hire a site-coordinator who will work with us at FFHS, on-site, every day. Somewhere out there is an optimistic, dynamic, hard-working person, that needs to apply for this job! I am told, the YMCA is planning to hold this posting open until next Friday, September 13th. While we are in collaboration with the YMCA, this posting is not employment with FFLSD. Interested persons should apply with the YMCA at: https://myy.org/jobs/ Scroll down and click on the: “21st Century Site Coordinator - Felicity-Franklin High School“ posting.

We are looking forward to welcoming our Freshman(9th) and 5th grade Cardinals back to school this coming Monday, August 19th beginning at 7:30am and ending at 11:30am. Bus transportation both to and from school will be provided as well as breakfast and lunch for all students.

Both 9th and 5th grade orientation days will be filled with fun activities and helpful advice to ensure our students have a successful transition into Middle & High School.

All other grades, will officially start the first day of school on Tuesday, August 20th.
It’s a great day to be a Cardinal!

post_text:
Good evening Felicity-Franklin Families,

We wanted to first communicate our deepest sympathies and sincere thoughts for the men, women and families of the Clermont County Sheriff’s Department.

We also wanted you to know that we are planning to discuss our support plan tomorrow morning and encourage the involvement of staff and students in the coming days. This will allow us to speak to all students and staff, ensuring that we have consistent and respectful communication throughout our school family.

There will be some tough days ahead, together we can help each other and honor those who serve us at such great personal cost.

post_text:
Good afternoon students,

Unfortunately, we must postpone the homecoming dance a second time. In fairness, the noon weather report calls for rain and freezing rain to begin in our area throughout the morning hours and then becoming snow around 5-8pm with the heaviest snowfall to occur from 8pm-midnight. After the snow moves through temperatures will drop to brutally cold temperatures through the rest of the weekend. These will not be safe conditions for you to be out in, I care about your safety.

Student safety is my number one priority. In fairness, to all our volunteers, parents who must pick-up flowers, hair appointments, picture and dinner arrangements, etc. This decision needs to come no later than lunchtime the day preceding.

The dance is rescheduled for next Saturday, 1/26/2019 from 8-11pm in the Elementary Cafetorium.

If you're traveling to CNE tonight to support the basketball team, travel safe, I look forward to seeing you there.

Please stay safe and warm this weekend.
BW

ATTENTION Students attending PROM!

Please sign-up for and plan on joining us for After-Prom! You can use this form OR visit the High School Office today.

https://goo.gl/forms/qStNF7etQmBpo23g2

After-Prom is going to be held on-campus in the Felicity-Franklin Elementary Gym and Cafetorium this year from Midnight to 4am.

After-Prom is a safe place for our students to have FUN!!!

Students must arrive by 1am and are not permitted to leave before 3:30am. We will have numerous prizes (including Apple Watch, TV, MK Clutch, Mini Fridge, and soooooo much more!) for students to win and games (Bungee Run , joust, corn hole tournament, ping pong, karaoke, video games, plinko, self-booth, and MORE!!!) to play!

Also, we will have a school bus available to pick students up at the conclusion of Prom and transport them back to FFHS.

post_text:
FYI - The following message will be delivered by one call at 5pm-9pm today.

Good afternoon, this is Felicity High School Principal Bob Walker calling to invite ALL 8th through 11th grade students to the scheduling fair, this Thursday evening, February 15th from 5-7pm in the high school auditeria.

All 8th through 11th grade students will receive a future planning tool containing personalized information about their education. Students and families will be able to speak with school staff about their interest, course options, and begin their scheduling process for next school year.

Additionally, we will have free fair foods (Hamburgers, Hot-dogs, French Fries, Popcorn & Cotton Candy) and door prize giveaways throughout the evening! You could win one of several prizes including some cool “Frogskins” sunglasses, a Samsung Chromebook, or a set of “Beats” headphones!

Don’t miss out on this opportunity to plan for your future! I look forward to seeing ALL 8th -11th grade students and families this Thursday, from 5-7pm in the high school auditeria for the Scheduling Fair!
